Luxury yacht operation in Istanbul!
Eight yachts for $160 million confiscated
The operation, carried out by customs teams in Istanbul, confiscated 8 yachts sold from one foreign country to another and should not enter the customs zone of Turkey.
According to a written statement from the Ministry of Customs and Trade, the operation by the Istanbul Customs and Trade Regional Directorate and the Istanbul Maritime Customs Protection Directorate of Trafficking and Intelligence determined that Ö.E.A., a Turkish citizen based in Turkey, bought 8 yachts from France and received them on behalf of the shell company from Haydarpaşa Customs by "renting".
Following the examination by customs conservation teams, it was discovered that Ö.E.A. brought the yachts to sell in Turkey.
8 yachts sold from one foreign country to another and should not enter the customs zone of Turkey, and items containing them, such as service boats, radar systems, generators, were confiscated.
The total customsed value of the seized motor yachts was determined to be 160 million liras.
